LOL--reminds me of what my 6 yo said yesterday...

"Mom, what's that little shirt called that people
where under their normal shirt?"

Me, thinking...."You mean an undershirt?"

Her...."Yeah..."....Thinking.....

"There are underpants and undershirts....Why don't we
call socks 'undershoes'?"

lol
Dana

messages.subject: behinds
messages.msgSnippet: Janene says last night... mom, do you know you have a lot of behinds? Uh, no, Janene, what do you mean? Well, you have behind your elbow, behind your knee,
messages.messageBody:
Janene says last night..."mom, do you know you have a lot of behinds?"

"Uh, no, Janene, what do you mean?"

"Well, you have behind your elbow, behind your knee, behind your hand,
behind your head, behind your back, and more!"

I laughed and said it was a good joke.

"It's not a joke, mama, it's true, I was just lying here thinking about
it and it's true!"

Joylyn
